	<Title>
		Recipe: Steak with steamed vegetables, soba noodles and ginger sauce
	</Title>
	<Abstract />
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Soba noodles &amp;mdash; Japanese noodles made with buckwheat and wheat flour &amp;mdash; have a dark brown-gray color. Here they&apos;re topped with lean sirloin, fresh asparagus and broccoli florets to make a one-dish meal.&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;Lightly coat a large, nonstick frying pan with cooking spray. Over high heat, saute the strips of steak until slightly pink, about 5 minutes. Set aside on a covered platter to keep warm.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fill a large pot 3/4 full with water and simmer. Add the soba noodles and cook until almost tender, about 10 minutes, or according to package directions. Drain the pasta thoroughly. Rinse the noodles and drain again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, in a large pot fitted with a steamer basket, bring 1 inch of water to a boil. Add the asparagus and broccoli florets, cover and steam until tender, about 10 minutes. Add the vegetables to the noodles and toss gently to mix evenly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To make the sauce, in a small saucepan over medium heat combine the soy sauce, rice wine vinegar, sesame oil, ginger, sugar and pepper. Heat until warmed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Divide the noodle-vegetable mixture onto warmed plates. Add the strips of steak and drizzle with the sauce. Serve immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;p&gt;8 ounces loin steak, cut into 1/2-inch strips&lt;br /&gt;
4 ounces dry soba noodles&lt;br /&gt;
2 cups chopped fresh asparagus, cut into 1-inch segments&lt;br /&gt;
2 cups broccoli florets&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the sauce&lt;br /&gt;
1/2 cup reduced-sodium soy sauce&lt;br /&gt;
1/3 cup rice wine vinegar&lt;br /&gt;
1 tablespoon sesame oil&lt;br /&gt;
2 tablespoons freshly grated ginger root, peeled&lt;br /&gt;
1 teaspoon sugar&lt;br /&gt;
Cracked black pepper, to taste&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Ingredients>
